  <div id="tribute-info" class="tribute-info">
    <div class="heading">
      <h2>
         Few acheivments of Nickola Tesla are listed below:
      </h2>
    </div>
    <fieldset class="points">
    <div class="point-1">
      <ul>
        <li><span class="headline">Radio communication:</span> Tesla was a pioneer in the field of radio communication.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="point-2">
      <ul>
        <li ><span class="headline">Tesla coil:</span> Tesla patented the Tesla coil in the late 1800s, which is still used in radio technology today and established the foundation for wireless technology.
      </li>
    </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="point-3">
      <ul>
        <li>
          <span class="headline">X-rays:</span> Tesla sent X-ray images of the human body to RÃ¶ntgen, and described some clinical benefits of X-rays, such as detecting lung diseases and determining the position of foreign objects.
        </li>
      <ul>
    </div>
    <div class="point-4">
      <ul>
        <li>
          <span class="headline">Alternating Current (AC) Electrical System:</span> Tesla's development and promotion of alternating current (AC) power transmission system revolutionized electrical engineering and laid the foundation for modern electrical distribution systems. His work on AC power made it possible to transmit electricity over long distances efficiently, enabling the widespread adoption of electricity.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="point-5">
      <ul>
        <li>
          <span class="headline">Wireless Power Transmission:</span> Tesla experimented with wireless power transmission, proposing the concept of transmitting electrical power without wires over long distances. While his ambitious Wardenclyffe Tower project aimed to demonstrate this technology, it was never completed due to financial difficulties.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </fieldset>
  </div>
  <div class="quote">
    <p>"Reading Tesla's works we continually come upon his numerous suggestions which have foreseen later developments in the area of radio technology."</p>
    <div class="name"><span >~Louis Cohen.</span></div>
  </div>
